  "body": "**Description**\r\n\r\nWhen playing a fault dispute game, the `op-challenger` needs to know the game depth for trace index and other game state calculations. Currently, this value is passed into the challenger via a CLI Flag `--game-depth`.\r\n\r\nInstead of manually providing this game depth, the challenger should fetch the game depth via the `Loader` fault component on initialization and bubble up the error on failure.\r\n\r\nSince the game depth is required for the initialization of the `Agent` fault component, it should be retrieved prior within the service component initialization.\r\n\r\n### Tasks\r\n- [ ] Implement a `FetchGameDepth` method on the `Loader` component.\r\n- [ ] Unit test the new `FetchGameDepth` loader component method.\r\n- [ ] On service init, fetch the game depth from the loader and pass this through to the Agent creation.\r\n\r\n**Tests**\r\n\r\nUnit tests implemented for the `Loader` component.\r\n\r\n**Associated Linear Ticket**\r\n\r\nCLI-4330\r\n",
